artifactory:index/permissionTarget:Permi.description:
## # Artifactory Permission Target Resource

**Requires Artifactory >= 6.6.0. If using a lower version see here**

Provides an Artifactory permission target resource. This can be used to create and manage Artifactory permission targets.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage
{{% example %}}

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as artifactory from "@pulumi/artifactory";

// Create a new Artifactory permission target called testpermission
const test_perm = new artifactory.PermissionTarget("test-perm", {
    build: {
        actions: {
            users: [{
                name: "anonymous",
                permissions: [
                    "read",
                    "write",
                ],
            }],
        },
        includesPatterns: ["**"],
        repositories: ["artifactory-build-info"],
    },
    repo: {
        actions: {
            groups: [{
                name: "readers",
                permissions: ["read"],
            }],
            users: [{
                name: "anonymous",
                permissions: [
                    "read",
                    "write",
                ],
            }],
        },
        excludesPatterns: ["bar/**"],
        includesPatterns: ["foo/**"],
        repositories: ["example-repo-local"],
    },
});
```
